The paper deals with efficient management and processing of large datasets, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of Bloom filters and reservoir sampling also suggests a focus on probabilistic data structures and algorithms, which falls under cs.CR. The paper also mentions applications in telecommunication call data records and online transaction records, which are common in information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper presents theoretical analysis and empirical evaluation, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG).
